00:46:23.250 --> 00:46:24.550
Kind of abandoned him.

00:46:24.550 --> 00:46:25.870
Whether it was the
arrogance of power.

00:46:25.870 --> 00:46:27.270
That, you know, the
longer you're in power.

00:46:27.270 --> 00:46:31.890
And he just kind of dismissed
their, I don't need to worry.

00:46:31.890 --> 00:46:33.190
It's really okay.

00:46:33.190 --> 00:46:34.740
I'm in, I'm here.

00:46:34.740 --> 00:46:37.430
So the combination
of the nationalism

00:46:37.430 --> 00:46:40.720
that was unleashed among the
republics, the Baltics first.

00:46:40.720 --> 00:46:44.460
The real difficulties
of economic change.

00:46:44.460 --> 00:46:48.880
His commitment to Glasnost which
opened up the political process.

00:46:48.880 --> 00:46:52.050
And, and not, one of
the expressions I take

00:46:52.050 --> 00:46:54.310
out of the business leadership
literature that relates

00:46:54.310 --> 00:46:55.960
to Gorbachev and to Rabin.

00:46:55.960 --> 00:46:57.950
Is the need to control
the temperature

00:46:57.950 --> 00:46:59.660
and keep the opposition close.

00:46:59.660 --> 00:47:01.800
This is in some of
the leadership books

00:47:01.800 --> 00:47:03.740
that are written in
the business community.

00:47:03.740 --> 00:47:05.460
And neither one of
those did that.

00:47:05.460 --> 00:47:06.910
And I think Gorbachev's
challenge,

00:47:06.910 --> 00:47:09.450
I think Rabin could've, his
was a little more manageable.

00:47:09.450 --> 00:47:11.850
But I, so that's one I'd
probably nominate is,

00:47:11.850 --> 00:47:14.740
is the most difficult
to really consolidate.

00:47:14.740 --> 00:47:17.620
So that he's disappeared,
you know?

00:47:17.620 --> 00:47:18.920
I guarantee you,
and first or all,

00:47:18.920 --> 00:47:21.290
you know, when he passes away.

00:47:21.290 --> 00:47:25.480
There will be enormous
accolades all over the world,

00:47:25.480 --> 00:47:27.100
except for inside
his own country.

